FBIS3-30143 "dreas038_h_94001" FBIS-EAS-94-038 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Feb 1994 Brunei, Malaysia & Singapore Malaysia Troops Arrive in Bosnia After Delay in Croatia BK2502085794 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0800 GMT 25 Feb 94 BK2502085794 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] A total of 500 Malaysian troops serving with the United Nations, UN, have been deployed in Bosnia-Herzegovina after being delayed in Croatia. Defense Minister Datuk Sri Najib Tun Razak said 65 men in two platoons were deployed around the Mount Igman area overlooking the besieged capital of Sarajevo while the rest were in Konjic and Visoko. He said the delay was due to the land route through neighboring Croatia to Bosnia proper being blocked by obstacles and the winter weather conditions. He told this to reporters after receiving 7,200 packets of goodies for the end of Ramadan celebration. The goodies will be flow by Hercules transport aircraft to the Malaysian troops in Bosnia. A total of 2,555 Malaysian military personnel are serving with the UN peacekeeping operation worldwide, including Somalia and their staff officers at the world body headquarters in New York.
